content:
To see Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect usage and billing in your contact center, check out these Salesforce and Amazon Connect resources.

Salesforce billing and usage reports include telephony minutes and Service Cloud Voice minutes. See Salesforce Reports for Amazon Connect Usage and Billing.
Voice call reports are run on the VoiceCall object to get voice call information, such as call ID, start and end times, duration, resolution status, conversation transcription, and recording.
The Salesforce CRM Analytics app views key performance indicators (KPIs) and sees graphs and data about your companyâ€™s Service Cloud Voice contact centers. Supervisors track call volume, average handle time, average speed to answer, and more. Admins customize how the contact center data appears.
Amazon Connect historical metrics reports view data about completed activity and performance in your contact center. Build custom reports to see other information.
Amazon Connect contract trace records capture events associated with a contact in your contact center. View these records to see transactional metrics, such as hold time, wait time, and agent interaction time.
title: Check Service Cloud Voice Usage and Billing
